git-reword (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: Preserve git remotes during commit message rewriting
  * Fix: Remove --partial flag to fully replace commits instead of mixing old and new history
  * Fix: Ensure git log shows same commit count after rewriting (old commits fully replaced)
  * Improvement: Automatically save and restore remotes before/after filter-repo runs

